## Step 1: Sender Profile Configuration

**Time:** 5 minutes
**Who does it:** You (during onboarding call) or the dealership (via dashboard Settings → Sender Profiles)

Every CEM the dealership sends must identify the sender per CASL s.6(2). Configure at least one sender profile with:

- **sender_name** — dealership name as it appears on emails/texts
- **mailing_address** — physical address
- **phone** — dealership phone number in E.164 format (+1XXXXXXXXXX)
- **email** — general contact email
- **website_url** — dealership website
- **is_default** — set to true for the primary profile

**API call:**
```
POST /api-sender-profiles
Authorization: Bearer {api_key}
```

**What to verify:**
- Response returns 201 with all fields populated
- is_default is true
- All three contact methods (phone, email, website_url) are present — this maximizes the sender_profile_completeness score

**Dealership-friendly explanation:**
> "This is your business card for emails and texts. CASL requires every marketing message to identify who sent it, with your name, address, and a way for people to contact you. We're setting that up now so every message you send through Nod automatically includes it."

